trend_summary: Imagery shows steady suburbanisation: forested interior gives way to curvilinear housing estates, road widening and a sizable new industrial platform in the southeast. Western sector is recently cleared, replacing woodland with bare or cultivated ground. Built-up footprint expands 15-25 %, yet extensive tree cover keeps overall character semi-green and moderately dense.
notable_changes: Progressive residential infill along curving street network across centre and east
Expansion of light-industrial/warehousing complex near the southeastern corner
Widening and extension of arterial roads improving internal connectivity
Large-scale tree clearing in the northwest, shifting to bare or agricultural land
Minor greening and parkland preservation pockets maintained amid new builds
